==English==
===Noun===
'''gerundive'''

#(''in Latin grammar''): a [[verbal]] [[adjective]]

The gerundive does not have a direct equivalent in English which has the [[gerund]] but not the gerundive.  In Latin the gerundive form implies a sense of necessity. For example, the word [[agenda]] is really a gerundive since it is those "things which must be done" not "just things to be done"

